value.0: What? What do you want? Get out of here!
What? You say you have a package from Roy for me? Well, let's see it then.
Scram, then!
Good, good. Now get out of here.
I don't have anything for you. Go talk to Roy Moss if you want a reward. Now scram!
What do you want?
You sure ask a lot of questions. I have a deal going down soon and I'm supposed to meet my client here.
I guess since you're involved now it doesn't matter if you know. Yes, this package contains some less-than-legal stims I'm trying to get transported off-planet.
You're just really itching to get involved, aren't ya? Thanks, but no thanks. I have a deal with this guy and I intend on keeping it.

I guess if you're running packages for us now then I can tell you. This is the headquarters of Coxxion, a smuggling organization. We're a small group but there's a surprising amount of work on this planet.

[He looks you up and down for a moment.] You? Don't make me laugh. Doing one run with us won't change the fact that you're a nobody here. But that decision isn't up to me, I suppose. Tell you what, you run another errand for me and I'll let you inside.

I've got a contact in Veles. Now listen closely. When you speak to him, he will say "Nice breeze we're having". Your response must be this phrase: "There is no breeze among the stars". Understand so far?
He will reply with "The stars know no bounds." Your reply must be "But bounds we must cross." Still with me?

For the final test he will ask you who sent you. You must use my name - Denam Reyholm - and no one else's. He'll give you what you need. Bring it back to me and we'll continue your little initiation process. Don't screw this up. Understand?
How goes your little project?
I don't know his real name or what he looks like. I only know he goes by "L" and he's somewhere in Veles. You'll need to look around for him yourself.
So, what did he give you in return?
[He dusts off the tome and stares at it intently, lost in thought.]

[He snaps back to reality.] Yes, yes. I apologize. For a moment there, I thought... [He trails off for a moment.] No, it's nothing. I don't have any use for that old book. Why don't you hang on to it. I sense it will serve you better.

Right. A deal's a deal. I'll unlock the door for you. [He slides a key card through the nearby terminal.] Not a word about what you see or hear in there, understood? Just give my name to whoever is working there today.
Not a word about what you see or hear inside, got it?
Sorry, my mistake. I don't have a package to deliver to you.
Here you go. [Deliver the package]
[Leave]
How about a reward?
[Leave]
Nothing.
Why are you out here?
Is that what the package was?
I see. Thanks for the information.
I could take it off planet for you.
What is this building?
A good organization needs good smugglers. How about taking on another one?
Let me think about it.
I'll do it.
I understand. Then what?
Yes. What's next?
I'll be back soon.
I'm still working on it.
What are the secret phrases again?
Where can I find your contact? What's his name?
I'll be back when I've found him.
I spoke to your contact in Veles.
A book, some kind of old tome. He said you'd want it back.
Uh, Denam, sir? Are you alright?
About letting me into this building...
Thank you.
